CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 14, 1958, pg. B7, reads: "MECHANICAL ENGINEERS - Seen joking on the Carnegie Tech campus before receiving their Master of Science in Mechanical Engineering are, left to right: James L. Rider of Baldwin Borough; M. Lucius Walker Jr. of Washington, D.C.; John D. Offutt of Jamaica N.Y.; Louis Raymond of Natrona, and Ben Schaltenbrand Jr. of Glenshaw."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of James L. Rider, M. Lucius Walker Jr., John D. Offutt, Louis Raymond, and Ben Schaltenbrand wearing dark caps and gowns, recipients of Master of Science in Mechanical Engineering Degrees, at Carnegie Institute of Technology [Carnegie Mellon University] graduation
